15/1101036220_0:230:3072:1958_1920x0_80_0_0_1b7603e4a4e3772112e9a800c4ea2e9c.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/09/15/1101036220_0:230:3072:1958_640x0_80_0_0_b99ee88add512589a0d18a4007805285.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/09/15/1101036220_0:230:3072:1958_1280x0_80_0_0_e0ed9603dbde313c1fd3731a9dce1969.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/09/15/1101036220_0:230:3072:1958_1920x0_80_0_0_1b7603e4a4e3772112e9a800c4ea2e9c.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / Viktor Antonyuk</div> / </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">俄罗斯喀山（人造卫星）网：乌克兰军队蓄意计划突破阿尔乔莫夫斯克市的侧翼，使俄罗斯军队在该市的推进复杂化，但正在采取“详尽措施”来阻止它，代理负责人丹尼斯·普希林 (Denis Pushilin)顿涅茨克人民共和国（DPR）周五告诉人造卫星。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “敌人现在正蓄意突破侧翼，为阿尔乔莫夫斯克本身和城里的人创造困难条件。因此，当然，正在采取彻底的措施，”他说。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">普希林最近告诉俄罗斯卫星通讯社，阿尔乔莫夫斯克侧翼的情况正在好转，侧翼的增援已经证明是有效的。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位官员还详细说明，基辅试图用来为阿尔乔莫夫斯克的部队提供补给的恰西夫亚尔市和阿尔乔莫夫斯克市之间的道路仍然很复杂，但处于俄罗斯军方的火力控制之下。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “[路上的情况]很复杂，但道路在我们部队的火力控制下，”普希林说。 “敌人没有畅通无阻的道路。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110450085" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/ukraine-planning-to-break-through-flanks-in-artyomovsk-to-curtail-russias-advance---dpr-head-1110450085.html?share-block=1110450587" data-title="&quot;[The situation on the road] is complicated, but the road is under fire control of our units,&quot; Pushilin said. &quot;The enemy has no unimpeded pass down the road.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">俄罗斯国防部 5 月 5 日表示，乌克兰军方曾试图用它为阿尔乔莫夫斯克的士兵提供弹药并部署更多部队，但恰西夫亚尔附近的一座桥已被摧毁。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Psuhilin 的顾问 Yan Gagin 早些时候说，大量乌克兰军队和装备集中在 Chasiv Yar 本身。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 19 May 2023 00:21:09 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/ukraine-planning-to-break-through-flanks-in-artyomovsk-to-curtail-russias-advance---dpr-head-1110450085.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/ukraine-planning-to-break-through-flanks-in-artyomovsk-to-curtail-russias-advance---dpr-head-1110450085.html<category>俄罗斯在乌克兰的特别行动</category><category>丹尼斯·普希林</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>民主共和国</category><category>乌克兰危机</category><category>士兵</category><category>顿涅茨克人民共和国</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Wisconsin Issues Air Quality Warning Amid Raging Wildfires in Canada]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110449522" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103915/33/1039153303_0:0:1813:1000_1440x900_80_0_1_2d703bf321a30bbd92718e57b870ad8e.png?source-sid=" data-photoview-image-id="1039153302" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/wisconsin-issues-air-quality-warning-amid-raging-wildfires-in-canada-1110449522.html?share-img=1039153302"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://youtu.be/ieTQvIdG-Vo" title="YouTube/GlobalLeaks 新闻">YouTube/GlobalLeaks News</a></span><span class="photoview__desc-text">加拿大无法阻止巨大的野火烧毁艾伯塔省的城镇</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="" alt="Canada Can’t Stop Enormous Wildfires Burning Down Towns Across Alberta - Sputnik International, 1920, 18.05.2023" title="加拿大无法阻止巨大的野火烧毁艾伯塔省的城镇" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103915/33/1039153303_18:0:1796:1000_1920x0_80_0_0_e418b56f25240cbfdcc845b07c942d83.png" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103915/33/1039153303_18:0:1796:1000_640x0_80_0_0_502e8a354a1a4fdcb83c4518d30df114.png 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103915/33/1039153303_18:0:1796:1000_1280x0_80_0_0_d463f949aa214a432cc1140f6223f14f.png 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103915/33/1039153303_18:0:1796:1000_1920x0_80_0_0_e418b56f25240cbfdcc845b07c942d83.png 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://youtu.be/ieTQvIdG-Vo" title="YouTube/GlobalLeaks 新闻">YouTube/GlobalLeaks 新闻</a></div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶戈尔·沙波瓦洛夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_shapovalov_egor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a><a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.shapovalov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">加拿大西部省份（不列颠哥伦比亚省、阿尔伯塔省、萨斯喀彻温省）正在遭受灾难性的森林大火。目前的情况不仅对公民的健康构成威胁，而且对这些地区的经济活动构成威胁。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">威斯康星州自然资源部已对该州大部分地区发布空气质量咨询，以应对加拿大南部持续的野火。该建议将于周四午夜生效，并将持续到周五。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该警告延伸到威斯康星州北部地区之外，这些地区最近几天已经出现雾霾天气。它现在包括该州的西南部、中南部和东部地区，包括密尔沃基。随着北方空气继续南下，西部地区也有可能受到影响。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国国家气象局目前预测，从午夜开始，源自加拿大的野火烟雾将开始从西北向东南移动到威斯康星州南部和东部。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">预计颗粒物的浓度有时会迅速上升，但随着更清洁的空气进入该地区，浓度会逐渐下降。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>在高峰时段，空气质量指数预计将达到“对敏感人群不健康”的水平。气象局建议这些群体中的个人在这段时间内限制户外体育活动。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h2"><h2 class="article__h2">石油、天然气和求助</h2></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国媒体援引能源报道称，由于有消息称日产量约为 270 万桶的油砂田持续受到威胁，天然气生产基地也面临危险，因此主要参与者已联合减产至少 240,000 桶/日咨询公司 Rystad Energy。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">加拿大已请求国际社会帮助应对该国西部的大规模森林火灾。艾伯塔省正在遭受火灾，超过 50 万公顷的森林和草原已经被毁。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “艾伯塔省的局势仍然非常令人担忧和危险，”渥太华公共安全部长比尔布莱尔说，因为加拿大政府呼吁外国帮助。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110449522" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/wisconsin-issues-air-quality-warning-amid-raging-wildfires-in-canada-1110449522.html?share-block=1110449531" data-title="&quot;The situation in Alberta remains very worrying and dangerous,&quot; said Ottawa Public Safety Secretary Bill Blair, as the Canadian government appealed for foreign help."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据媒体报道，来自加拿大各地的约 2,500 名消防员和 400 名士兵已被派往艾伯塔省扑灭大火，但到目前为止，已有 27 起火灾失控。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 18 May 2023 23:08:03 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/wisconsin-issues-air-quality-warning-amid-raging-wildfires-in-canada-1110449522.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/wisconsin-issues-air-quality-warning-amid-raging-wildfires-in-canada-1110449522.html<category>美洲</category><category>加拿大</category><category>国家气象局</category><category>艾伯塔省</category><category>野火</category><category>抽烟</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Suspected Pentagon Leaker Was Repeatedly Warned About Improper Handling of Classified Docs]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110449322" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/1b/1109899023_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_665d6256b1a6ab0a0d5d984fc7f62d0e.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1109898960" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/suspected-pentagon-leaker-was-repeatedly-warned-about-improper-handling-of-classified-docs-1110449322.html?share-img=1109898960"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Margaret Small</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">马萨诸塞州空军国民警卫队成员杰克·特谢拉 (Jack Teixeira) 于 2023 年 4 月 19 日星期三出现在波士顿的美国地方法院。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="Massachusetts Air National Guardsman Jack Teixeira, seated second from right, appears in U.S. District Court, in Boston, Wednesday, April 19, 2023. - Sputnik International, 1920, 18.05.2023" title="2023 年 4 月 19 日，星期三，马萨诸塞州空军国民警卫队队员杰克·特谢拉 (Jack Teixeira) 出现在波士顿的美国地方法院。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/1b/1109899023_0:251:3072:1979_1920x0_80_0_0_16138f01d6240618688f4e70c85b2c45.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/1b/1109899023_0:251:3072:1979_640x0_80_0_0_017ff7001867c115fe215e239db4428c.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/1b/1109899023_0:251:3072:1979_1280x0_80_0_0_cedc50b55fb337de62938dbf79730642.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/1b/1109899023_0:251:3072:1979_1920x0_80_0_0_16138f01d6240618688f4e70c85b2c45.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Margaret Small </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">伊恩德马蒂诺</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_demartino_ian/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">美国空军飞行员杰克·特谢拉 (Jack Teixeira) 因涉嫌在名为 Thug Shaker Central 的 Discord 聊天室泄露机密文件而于 4 月被捕。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国检察官在法庭文件中称，疑似五角大楼泄密者杰克·特谢拉 (Jack Teixeira) 曾就其处理机密文件的行为受到空军上级至少两次警告。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">周三向公众公布的法庭文件支持特谢拉在等待审判期间继续被拘留。 Teixeria 没有提交正式的请求，他的辩护团队要求允许他在他父亲的住​​所居住直到他的审判。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p>检察官在法庭文件中写道：“特别是，即使在两次不同的场合受到上司的警告，被告的披露（以及相关的吹嘘）仍在继续。” “一次是在 2022 年 9 月，一次是在 2022 年 10 月”，原因是“被告采取的与机密信息相关的行动”。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110449322" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/suspected-pentagon-leaker-was-repeatedly-warned-about-improper-handling-of-classified-docs-1110449322.html?share-block=1110449325" data-title="“In particular, the Defendant’s disclosures (and associated boasting) continued even after being admonished by his superiors on two separate occasions,” prosecutors wrote in the court documents. “Once in September 2022 and once in October 2022,” due to “concerning actions that the Defendant took related to classified information.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">为了支持他们的说法，检察官提交了三份空军备忘录，记录了特谢拉处理机密文件的方式。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>首先，从 9 月开始，人们观察到特谢拉对机密文件做笔记，然后将这些笔记放入他的口袋。部分编辑的文件称，他随后被指示“不再以任何形式记录机密情报信息”。</p><p>一个月后，特谢拉的上司“意识到”他可能“无视关于深入情报的停止命令”。文件称，他参加了一次机密会议，并在被告知停止并“专注于他的工作”之前询问了有关信息的“非常具体的问题”。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">第三份文件称，特谢拉所在单位的一名上司观察到他正在查看与其主要工作职责无关的情报。他没有因为那件事受到训斥，但其他上司都知道了这件事。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>特谢拉的部队已停止执行情报任务，空军暂时停职了该部队的两名指挥官，等待对泄露的文件进行调查。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在泄露文件的 Discord 聊天室中，一名据称是特谢拉的用户最初提供了他写下的机密材料的摘要。在遇到聊天其他成员的怀疑后，该用户开始发布完整的文档。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">检察官辩称，空军备忘录表明特谢拉“故意无视”他保护机密信息的职责。辩护团队辩称，特谢拉从未打算“扰乱美国的地缘政治事务”，而且他从未打算将这些文件传播到他分享这些文件的 Discord 聊天之外。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>关于特谢拉继续被拘留的听证会定于周五举行。</strong></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 18 May 2023 22:50:59 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/suspected-pentagon-leaker-was-repeatedly-warned-about-improper-handling-of-classified-docs-1110449322.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/suspected-pentagon-leaker-was-repeatedly-warned-about-improper-handling-of-classified-docs-1110449322.html<category>美洲</category><category>杰克特谢拉</category><category>空军</category><category>五角大楼</category><category>机密文件</category><category>五角大楼泄密</category><category>不和谐</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Footage Captures Shocking Moment US Cop Clings to Car Roof After Arrest Attempt]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110447414" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/12/1110447690_0:0:1180:561_1440x900_80_0_1_7c02c955c6f749eeb67df1f5bef504bc.png?source-sid=cc_0" data-photoview-image-id="1110447672" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/footage-captures-shocking-moment-us-cop-clings-to-car-roof-after-arrest-attempt-1110447414.html?share-img=1110447672"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright"><a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/" title="CC0">CC0</a> / <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@PoliceActivity" title="警察活动">PoliceActivity</a> / <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WS_dE2SsUXs" title="截取的截屏以司机加速离开而警察在汽车引擎盖上结束">截取自 Traffic Stop Ends with Driver speed off with Cop Optop of Car Hood</a></span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">Officer Patrick McCarty trying to stop Dennis Guider Jr. while on the car&#39;s hood.</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="cc_0" alt="Officer Patrick McCarty trying to stop Dennis Guider Jr. while on the car's hood. - Sputnik International, 1920, 18.05.2023" title="帕特里克·麦卡蒂警官试图在汽车引擎盖上阻止小丹尼斯·古德。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/12/1110447690_92:0:1089:561_1920x0_80_0_0_efc76bddf3f0aec2a2efcd2726f9b1c6.png" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/12/1110447690_92:0:1089:561_640x0_80_0_0_dbc728954b43b7fe82e0d300878998ce.png 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/12/1110447690_92:0:1089:561_1280x0_80_0_0_029d802160c186a123045a8cc4e5c0b2.png 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/12/1110447690_92:0:1089:561_1920x0_80_0_0_efc76bddf3f0aec2a2efcd2726f9b1c6.png 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> <a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/" title="CC0">CC0</a> / <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@PoliceActivity" title="警察活动">PoliceActivity</a> / <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WS_dE2SsUXs" title="截取的截屏以司机加速离开而警察在汽车引擎盖上结束">交通拦截的截图以司机加速离开而警察在汽车引擎盖上结束</a></div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶戈尔·沙波瓦洛夫</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_shapovalov_egor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a><a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.shapovalov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">2021 年，在爱荷华州卡罗尔的一次例行交通拦截中，一名被通缉的男子在视频中捕捉到的一起令人震惊的事件中避开了警察。在最近的听证会上，被告的律师辩称，这名男子不知道在涉及移动的情况下如何表现车辆。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">新发布的镜头提供了对 2021 年事件的深入了解，在该事件中，一名爱荷华州警察在例行交通停车出现问题后拼死抓住车顶。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">卡罗尔警察局发布的视频显示，警官帕特里克·麦卡蒂 (Patrick McCarty) 与被捕者小丹尼斯·古德 (Dennis Guider Jr.) 就伊利诺伊州未完成的逮捕令对质。然而，Guider 没有服从，而是打开了司机的车门，推出了一名一直在驾驶车辆的女性并加速，促使 McCarty 在汽车开始远离现场时跳上了汽车的引擎盖。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">麦卡蒂急切地想要阻止 Guider，他一边拔出枪支一边紧贴车顶大喊让他停下来。新闻稿中包含的其他镜头不仅包括佩戴在身上的录音，还包括行车记录仪视频，显示麦卡蒂在被扔到车顶之前暂时跪在汽车引擎盖上。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">更多的警车加入了追捕，但只持续了大约一分钟。在 Guider 变成砾石地并驶过一条沟渠后，McCarty 最终被看到被扔到地上。麦卡蒂背部骨折，在圣安东尼地区医院接受治疗。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="social" data-social="youtube"><div class="article__youtube"><iframe width="100%" height="100%" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/WS_dE2SsUXs" webkitallowfullscreen="webkitAllowFullScreen" mozallowfullscreen="mozallowfullscreen" allowfullscreen="allowFullScreen" frameborder="0" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">事件发生两年后，Guider 于 2023 年 3 月认罪。在宣判期间，Guider 的律师主张宽大处理，声称 McCarty 没有接受过有关如何处理涉及移动车辆的情况的适当培训。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “在警官拔出枪并跳到我汽车的引擎盖上后，我担心自己的生命安全，”Guider 在 2 月份写给卡罗尔县法院书记员的一封信中写道。他还指出，他在交通拦截期间没有携带武器。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110447414" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/footage-captures-shocking-moment-us-cop-clings-to-car-roof-after-arrest-attempt-1110447414.html?share-block=1110449492" data-title="“I feared for my life after the officer pull[ed] out his gun and jump[ed] on the hood of my car,” Guider wrote in a letter to the Carroll County clerk of court in February. He also noted that he had been unarmed during the traffic stop."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Guider 于 5 月 11 日被判刑，最高刑期为五年，与他在伊利诺伊州的刑期不同。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 18 May 2023 22:22:03 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/footage-captures-shocking-moment-us-cop-clings-to-car-roof-after-arrest-attempt-1110447414.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/footage-captures-shocking-moment-us-cop-clings-to-car-roof-after-arrest-attempt-1110447414.html<category>超越政治</category><category>我们</category><category>病毒性的</category><category>警察</category><category>追赶</category><category>追车</category><category>警方追捕</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Biden Admin Frets About 'Optics' Amid Illegal Immigration Surge Post-Title 42]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110445879" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/02/1110029759_0:0:3071:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_067d5463c1bbcd20be21fc722ba772e0.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1110029741" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/biden-admin-frets-about-optics-amid-illegal-immigrant-surge-post-title-42-1110445879.html?share-img=1110029741"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / STRINGER</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">来自中美洲和南美洲的移民参加了试图到达墨西哥-美国边境的大篷车，同时进行 viacrucis 以抗议在北部城市拘留中心发生的火灾中 40 名移民的死亡2023 年 4 月 23 日，墨西哥南部恰帕斯州塔帕丘拉的华雷斯</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="Migrants from Central and South America take part in a caravan attempting to reach the Mexico-US border, while carrying out a viacrucis to protest for the death of 40 migrants in a fire at a detention center in the northern city of Juarez, in Tapachula, Chiapas state, southern Mexico, on April 23, 2023 - Sputnik International, 1920, 18.05.2023" title="来自中美洲和南美洲的移民参加了试图到达墨西哥-美国边境的大篷车，同时在塔帕丘拉北部城市华雷斯的一个拘留中心进行 viacrucis 抗议 40 名移民在火灾中丧生， 2023 年 4 月 23 日，墨西哥南部恰帕斯州" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/02/1110029759_0:161:3071:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_ba0abc19f4cf235a11cf644e205ba64e.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/02/1110029759_0:161:3071:1888_640x0_80_0_0_07b4a124db798887c04016cacb5662f8.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/02/1110029759_0:161:3071:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_ffb03248ed7d2f41e82b7888e5b21bb4.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/02/1110029759_0:161:3071:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_ba0abc19f4cf235a11cf644e205ba64e.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / 斯特林格</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-image"><img media-type="s150x150" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="James Tweedie - Sputnik International" title="詹姆斯·特威迪" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/1c/1080307270_0:3:397:400_100x100_80_0_0_7777393b9b18802f2e3c5eaa9cbcc612.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">詹姆斯·特威迪</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_tweedie_james/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:j.tweedie@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">高级国家安全研究员兼作家托德·本斯曼 (Todd Bensmann) 多年来一直在记录边境墨西哥一侧的非法移民。他说，政府和主流媒体忽视这个问题的时间太长了。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">一位国家安全专家表示，拜登白宫只担心墨西哥边境移民危机的“光学”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">上周，根据美国疾病控制和预防中心的命令，允许将陆路非法抵达的移民驱逐出境的规定因担心他们可能携带 COVID-19 而被取消。此后，这一事态发展引发了人们对跨越美墨边境的前所未有的人口贩运浪潮的担忧。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>托德·本斯曼</strong>告诉<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/theres-a-reason-americans-hate-washington-dc-1110428776.html" target="_blank">人造卫星</a>，拜登政府“正在让他们进来，并奖励他们入境和长期逗留，以奖励他们对走私费的投资。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">他说，非法移民案件中使用的“主要漏洞”是“弗洛雷斯定居点”，这是最高法院 1993 年的一项裁决，该裁决防止当局将被贩运的儿童关押超过短时间。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “它基本上说我们不能长时间拘留家人，”本斯曼说。 “所以他们认为他们可以进来，我们会释放他们，在未来几年寻求庇护。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">专家解释说，第 42 条已经阻止移民“滥用”政治庇护制度以避免被驱逐出境。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “任何人真正想要的只是能够申请庇护。它让他们绕过所有其他规则和法律，然后绕过边境巡逻，然后他们就在这个国家，”本斯曼说。 “过去几年，大规模系统性庇护滥用 Title 42 的滥用暂停了。现在 Title 42 结束了，庇护又回来了。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110445879" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/biden-admin-frets-about-optics-amid-illegal-immigrant-surge-post-title-42-1110445879.html?share-block=1110446990" data-title="&quot;All anybody really wanted was to just be able to claim asylum. It gets them around all the other rules and laws and then around Border Patrol and then they're in the country,&quot; Bensmann said. &quot;There was a pause for the last couple of years in the abuse of massive systematic asylum abuse with Title 42. Now Title 42 is over and asylum is back.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位纪录片制片人说，第 42 集的结尾见证了主流媒体终于“出现在派对上”——尽管“晚了大约两年半”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “如果我是一名移民记者，我会住在边境两边，”本斯曼强调说。 “但事实并非如此。偶尔他们会空降，但他们永远不会真正解释发生了什么或任何事情。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “这一次他们至少掩盖了它，因为他们预计第二天会出现大的、丑陋的、可怕的激增，”他补充说。 “现在这种激增并没有实现。所以现在每个人都在庆祝胜利。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">虽然美国当局试图隐瞒危机的真实规模以避免媒体的负面报道，但本斯曼在边境的另一边工作，在那里他能够拍摄到每天都有成千上万的人穿过里奥格兰德河进入德克萨斯州，并在Title 42 到期前的准备工作。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “我在墨西哥方面进行报道，所以我没有那个问题。没有拜登政府担心政治光学。那里根本没有美国记者。所以我一个人，”他说. “我一直发现墨西哥是报道此事的地方，因为拜登政府肯定会尽一切可能隐藏大量移民的形象，所有这些都聚集在一起，表明问题有多么严重。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110445879" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/biden-admin-frets-about-optics-amid-illegal-immigrant-surge-post-title-42-1110445879.html?share-block=1110446991" data-title="&quot;I do my reporting on the Mexican side, so I don't have that problem. There's no Biden administration that's worried about the political optics. And there were no American reporters over there at all. So I was all alone,&quot; he said. &quot;I've always found that Mexico was the place to report this, because the Biden administration definitely does everything it possibly can to hide the optics of huge numbers of migrants, all in a big gathering together that shows how gigantic the problem is.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>有关时事的更深刻评论，请查看或人造卫星广播节目<em><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/radio-the-backstory/" target="_blank">The Backstory。</a></em></strong></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 18 May 2023 22:05:30 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/biden-admin-frets-about-optics-amid-illegal-immigrant-surge-post-title-42-1110445879.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/biden-admin-frets-about-optics-amid-illegal-immigrant-surge-post-title-42-1110445879.html<category>美洲</category><category>我们</category><category>美墨边境</category><category>墨西哥</category><category>移民</category><category>非法移民</category><category>贩卖人口</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>疾病控制与预防中心 (CDC)</category><category>美国疾病控制中心 (CDC)</category><category>里奥格兰德</category><category>得克萨斯州</category><category>美国疾病控制和预防中心</category><category>寻求庇护者</category><category>庇护申请</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Disney Scraps Planned Florida Corporate Campus Amid DeSantis Feud]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110448972" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/04/14/1094923207_0:0:3071:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_6f8f44522e96010934489e150f0a2a53.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1094923203" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/disney-scraps-planned-florida-corporate-campus-amid-desantis-feud-1110448972.html?share-img=1094923203"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / John Raoux</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2021 年 8 月 30 日星期一，在佛罗里达州布埃纳维斯塔湖，人们看到沃尔特迪斯尼世界魔法王国新粉刷的灰姑娘城堡与徽章一起庆祝主题公园成立 50 周年</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="The newly painted Cinderella Castle at the Magic Kingdom at Walt Disney World is seen with the the crest to celebrate the 50th anniversary of the theme park Monday, Aug. 30, 2021, in Lake Buena Vista, Fla - Sputnik International, 1920, 18.05.2023" title="2021 年 8 月 30 日星期一，在佛罗里达州布埃纳维斯塔湖，可以看到沃尔特迪斯尼世界魔法王国新粉刷的灰姑娘城堡带有徽章，以庆祝主题公园成立 50 周年" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/04/14/1094923207_0:161:3071:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_2f924c664f61e768c397841d4a472451.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/04/14/1094923207_0:161:3071:1888_640x0_80_0_0_16835ea7d467ab2ebf332a773e872421.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/04/14/1094923207_0:161:3071:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_c6297c6207a6aae5400fe0a7f6df11cc.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/04/14/1094923207_0:161:3071:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_2f924c664f61e768c397841d4a472451.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / John Raoux </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">芳汀嘉迪尼耶</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_gardinier_fantine/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">华特迪士尼公司 (Walt Disney Co.) 在损失了数十亿美元的流媒体收入后，正在裁员 7,000 多名员工，而近年来该公司在流媒体收入上投入了巨资。迪士尼在奥兰多郊外的华特迪士尼世界度假区雇佣了大约 77,000 名员工。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">迪士尼周四透露，它正在取消计划在佛罗里达州奥兰多附近投资 9 亿美元的企业园区，以及沃尔特迪斯尼世界的一个热门景点。这些决定是在佛罗里达州州长罗恩·德桑蒂斯 (Ron DeSantis) 签署一系列反 LGBTQ 立法后的第二天做出的，批评者称这些立法是“仇恨名单”，迪斯尼和州长政府长期以来一直不和。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据美国媒体报道，迪士尼员工周四收到一封电子邮件，宣布他们将不再搬迁至华特迪士尼计划建设的占地 60 英亩的诺娜湖园区。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “虽然有些人对新园区感到兴奋，但我知道这个决定及其周围的环境对其他人来说很困难，”迪士尼乐园、体验和产品部门负责人乔什·达马罗 (Josh D&#39;Amaro) 在电子邮件中说。 “鉴于自该项目宣布以来发生的相当大的变化，包括新的领导层和不断变化的业务条件，我们决定不再向前推进。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110448972" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/disney-scraps-planned-florida-corporate-campus-amid-desantis-feud-1110448972.html?share-block=1110448975" data-title="“While some were excited about the new campus, I know that this decision and the circumstances surrounding it have been difficult for others,” Josh D’Amaro, head of Disney’s Parks, Experiences and Products division, said in the email. “Given the considerable changes that have occurred since the announcement of this project, including new leadership and changing business conditions, we have decided not to move forward.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该项目将需要大约 2,000 名工人从加利福尼亚州南部搬迁，那里是迪斯尼的另一个主要美国公园沃尔特迪斯尼乐园所在​​的地方。然而，数百名迪士尼员工已经搬迁到奥兰多地区；据知情人士透露，他们现在可以选择搬回加州。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在另一封致奥兰多地区社区领袖的信中，华特迪士尼公司总裁杰夫瓦勒承诺“继续投资于我们的核心业务”。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “我们目前的计划要求我们在未来 10 年内向华特迪士尼世界投资 170 亿美元，并创造 13,000 个新工作岗位，以继续发挥我们作为酒店和主题娱乐行业领先雇主的作用，”Vahle 说。 “我们希望这些计划能够成为未来的现实。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110448972" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/disney-scraps-planned-florida-corporate-campus-amid-desantis-feud-1110448972.html?share-block=1110448979" data-title="“Our plans currently call for us to invest $17 billion in Walt Disney World over the next 10 years and create 13,000 new jobs to continue doing our part as a leading employer in the hospitality and themed entertainment industry,” Vahle said. “We hope those plans will become a future reality.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">另外，它还关闭了在沃尔特迪斯尼世界的银河星际巡洋舰体验，这是一个让粉丝沉浸在“星球大战”宇宙中几天的景点。这家酒店将于 9 月 28 日关闭，每对夫妇入住两晚的费用将近 5,000 美元。它开业仅一年前，即 2022 年 3 月。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">迪士尼没有进一步澄清其决定。然而，DeSantis 的办公室发表了一份声明，对该公司的决定幸灾乐祸，在因其反 LGBTQ 政策受到批评后，该公司与该公司的争执已经持续了一年多。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “大约两年前，迪士尼宣布了诺娜湖校区的可能性。该项目一无所获，该州不确定它是否会取得成果，”州长新闻秘书杰里米·雷德芬 (Jeremy Redfern) 在一份声明中说。 “鉴于公司的财务困境、市值下降和股价下跌，他们重组业务运营并取消不成功的企业也就不足为奇了。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110448972" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/disney-scraps-planned-florida-corporate-campus-amid-desantis-feud-1110448972.html?share-block=1110448982" data-title="“Disney announced the possibility of a Lake Nona campus nearly two years ago. Nothing ever came of the project, and the state was unsure whether it would come to fruition,” Jeremy Redfern, the governor’s press secretary, said in a statement. “Given the company’s financial straits, falling market cap and declining stock price, it is unsurprising that they would restructure their business operations and cancel unsuccessful ventures.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h2"><h2 class="article__h2"> “陷入老鼠陷阱”</h2></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">一天前，在反对同性恋恐惧症、双性恋恐惧症和跨性别恐惧症国际日，德桑蒂斯明确签署了几项法案，使其成为法律，这些法案严重限制了阳光之州 LGBTQ 人群的权利。这四项法案有效地禁止所有跨性别儿童和大多数跨性别成年人接受性别肯定护理；禁止跨性别者使用符合其性别认同的卫生间；并进一步限制公立学校对 LGBTQ 人群和话题的容忍度，包括扩大<u><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20220328/disney-pledges-to-help-repeal-dont-say-gay-law-after-floridas-desantis-signs-measure-1094272381.html" target="_blank">迪士尼去年抗议的</a></u>所谓“不要说同性恋”的法律。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>批评者将新法律称为“仇恨石板”，并呼吁抵制阳光之州。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">为了回应迪斯尼去年对其政策的批评，德桑蒂斯推动了一项注定失败的努力<u><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230402/disney-plies-legal-loophole-linked-to-king-charles-iii-to-dodge-desantis-self-governance-crackdown-1109042504.html" target="_blank">，即剥夺公司对监管沃尔特迪斯尼世界的特区的控制权</a></u>，用他亲自挑选的成员取代董事会，并推动立法取消迪斯尼的开发协议赋予公司对其财产和周边地区的自主权。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">作为回应， <u><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230426/raging-feud-disney-files-lawsuit-against-desantis-over-government-retaliation-1109864540.html" target="_blank">迪士尼起诉德桑蒂斯政府</a></u>，声称其行为违反了第一修正案。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">德桑蒂斯在共和党关于 2024 年总统大选的许多民意调查中都受到青睐，人们普遍预计他将在下周正式<u><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230427/report-desantis-gearing-up-for-2024-election-bid-in-early-may-1109868206.html" target="_blank">宣布他的竞选活动</a></u>。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">为了回应周三关于迪士尼的消息，特朗普的竞选团队发表了一份声明，对德桑蒂斯的“弱点”幸灾乐祸，称“失败的文化仍在继续”。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110448972" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/disney-scraps-planned-florida-corporate-campus-amid-desantis-feud-1110448972.html?share-block=1110448990" data-title="In response to the news about Disney on Wednesday, Trump’s campaign issued a statement gloating about DeSantis’ “weakness,” saying “the culture of losing continues.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">特朗普作战室在推特上写道：“罗恩叛逆被抓进了老鼠夹。”他使用了特朗普贬低他可能的竞选对手的绰号。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 18 May 2023 21:53:48 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/disney-scraps-planned-florida-corporate-campus-amid-desantis-feud-1110448972.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230518/disney-scraps-planned-florida-corporate-campus-amid-desantis-feud-1110448972.html<category>美洲</category><category>罗恩德桑蒂斯</category><category>华特迪士尼世界</category><category>同志</category><category>我们</category><category>佛罗里达</category><category>裁员</category></item></channel></rss>